SCENARIO-03 – Slow Laptop Due to High Disk Utilization
Business Context
A Horizon Freight Logistics warehouse workstation began experiencing severe performance degradation during peak operational hours, impacting inventory management and shipment processing.

Ticket Summary
Ticket ID: HD-0003
Category: Performance Issue
Impact: Single User
Urgency: Medium
Priority: P2
Device: Warehouse Workstation (Windows 11)

User Reported Issue
“My computer is extremely slow. Applications are freezing and the inventory system takes several minutes to load.”
CompTIA A+ Troubleshooting Methodology

1️⃣ Identify the Problem
System slow during login and application launch.
Task Manager shows disk usage consistently at 100%.
No visible hardware failure alerts.

2️⃣ Establish Theory
Possible causes considered:
Background Windows updates
Disk nearly full
Malware or excessive startup programs
Failing HDD

Most likely cause:
High disk utilization due to low available storage and excessive startup applications.

3️⃣ Test the Theory
Checked disk space: Only 4GB free of 256GB.
Identified large temporary files and outdated system backups.
Reviewed startup programs — multiple unnecessary applications enabled.
Ran quick malware scan — no threats detected.

Theory confirmed: Storage saturation causing performance bottleneck.

4️⃣ Plan of Action
Remove temporary files and outdated backups.
Uninstall unused applications.
Disable unnecessary startup programs.
Schedule disk cleanup maintenance.

5️⃣ Verify Functionality
Disk space increased to 52GB free.
Disk utilization reduced to normal range.
System boot time improved.
Inventory application loaded within acceptable timeframe.
User confirmed improved performance.

6️⃣ Document Findings
Root Cause:
Low available disk space and excessive startup applications causing sustained high disk utilization.

Resolution:
Freed storage space and optimized startup configuration.

Preventative Action:
Scheduled quarterly disk maintenance and user education on storage best practices.

Time to Resolve: 28 minutes

Business Impact
Warehouse operations restored to normal speed, preventing shipment delays.

Skills Demonstrated:
Performance troubleshooting
Disk utilization analysis
Startup process optimization
Malware validation
Preventative maintenance planning
Structured CompTIA troubleshooting methodology
